Concerning the norm we already have [RingOfIntegers.norm](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/NumberTheory/NumberField/Norm.html#RingOfIntegers.norm). Or do you mean something else?
Yes but I find the AKLB setup (as in this file) easier to work with and I plan to redefine RingOfIntegers.norm using the new definition.

This is a rather long definition. Maybe a good idea is to split it, defining the function and proving the various properties, and then packaging everything here (you can make everything `private` if you want).

```suggestion
- `galRestrictHom`: The restriction `Aut(L/K) → Aut(B/A)` as an `MulEquiv` in an ALKB setup.
```
And what does ALKB mean?
I guess it means A a subring of K and B a subring of L?

`galRestrict` is the main definition to use. Updated the docstring of `galRestrictHom` to make it clearer.
Also added a sentence in the module docstring explaining AKLB.
should the `?` still be on the simp?
Oh I didn't see the `says` so maybe I just don't know what this is.
Can you add here and in the definition of `galRestrictHom` that `galRestrict` should be preferred over `galRestrictHom`?
I think it is self evident since `galRestrictHom` is about `L →ₐ[K] L` where `galRestrict` is about `L ≃ₐ[K] L`. I think the reference of `galRestrict` in the docstring of `galRestrictHom` is enough?
